MQA.TileMap

Constructs an MQA.TileMap object.

Parameters

parent(HTML Element) A browser DIV HTML element to be the map’s container.
zoom(int) the initial zoom level of the map.
mqLatLng(MQA.LatLng) A point representing the center of the map.
mtype(string) The initial map type.  Possible values are ‘map’, ‘sat’, or ‘hyb’
mqmapinit(MQA.MapInit) Optional The object to hold the best fit implementation.

Note

The MQTileMap is the javascript objects that represents the functionality of a Mapquest draggable map.

See Also

getMapType

Example

var myMap = new MQA.TileMap(myDiv, 10, new MQA.LatLng(38.87308,-77.007558), 'map');

Parameters

none

See Also

removeShape

Removes the specified shape from the map’s default collection.  Fires the “MQA.TileMap.shapeRemoved” event.

Parameters

mqShape(MQA.Poi or MQA.ShapeOverlay) Shape to remove from the map.

See Also

getShapes, addShape, addShapes, removeAllShapes, replaceShapes

replaceShapes

Replaces the shapes in the map’s current default collection with the shapes in the specified collection.  Events are fired for each shape removed from the old collection and for each shape added from the new collection.  A “mapcleared” event also fires before adding the new shapes.

Parameters

shapeCollection(MQA.ShapeCollection) The collection of shapes to add.

See Also

addShape, addShapes, getShapes, removeShapes, removeAllShapes

zoomToRect

Zoom the map to the closest zoom level that fits the specified rectangle.

Parameters

rectLL(MQA.RectLL) The rectangle to use as a boundary
keepCenterOptional (boolean) Specify if the map should maintain its current center point.
minZoomOptional (int) Minimum zoom level to use even if the rect needs a lower zoom level to fit.
maxZoomOptional (int) Maximum zoom level to use even if the rect needs a higher zoom level to fit.

See Also

bestFit, bestFitLL, <getBoundingRect>

bestFit

Parameters

maxZoomLevelOptional Maximum zoom level

bestFitLL

Pans and Zooms the map to “best fit” to the nearest zoom level that allows all the specified Lat/Lngs to appear on the map.

Parameter

arrayLL(Array) An array of MQA.LatLng objects.
keepCenterOptional (boolean) Specifies whether to maintain the map’s center point.  Default is false.
minZoomLevel(int) Minimum allowed zoom level.
maxZoomLevel(int) Maximum allowed zoom level.

See Also

bestFit, zoomToRect, setBestFitMargin, getBestFitMargin

See Also

panToLatLng

Slides the mp to the new center specified.  If point is greater than 100 pixels out of map boundaries the map is snapped to center, otherwise the map will smooth scroll to new center.

Parameters

mqLatLng(MQA.LatLng) The new center point.

See Also

setCenter, getCenter
